//regular expression tester
https://regex101.com/
https://www.regexpal.com/


//regular expression tuts
^[a-z0-9\/]+$

^ : assert position at start of the string.
[] : match single character present in the set.
a-z : single character in the range between a and z
0-9 : single character in the range between 0 and 9
\/ : matches the character / literally
+ : matches between 1 and unlimited times, as many times as possible giving back as neededed (greedy) sample you type more letter aaaa it reads valid but if you'll used ^[a-z]$ w.o ( + Quantifier ) multiple aaa doesn't read only read the first a character.


